const classificationRequest = {
  model: 'claude-haiku-4-5-20251001',
  max_tokens: 1400,
  temperature: 0,
  system: 'You are an expert customer service AI for SpaceKiwi, an Etsy handmade goods shop run by Akriti. Analyze customer messages and identify ALL intents. Be conservative: when in doubt, escalate to a human rather than auto-reply.',
  messages: [{
    role: 'user',
    content: `# CUSTOMER MESSAGE
"${data.message_text}"

# PRODUCT CONTEXT
${listingText}

# SHOP POLICIES & FAQ
${faqContent}

# ORDER HISTORY
${ordersText}

# CONVERSATION HISTORY (context only)
${historyLines || 'No previous messages.'}

# TASK
Return a JSON object with these exact fields:
{
  "intents": [{"type": "Damage|Complaint|Refund|RushOrder|Shipping|Returns|Tracking|ProductQuestion|SimpleFAQ|CustomOrder|Exchange|Positive", "priority": "HIGH|MEDIUM|LOW", "description": "what customer is asking NOW", "answerable_from_context": true/false}],
  "primary_priority": "HIGH|MEDIUM|LOW",
  "recommended_action": "immediate_alert|batch_review|auto_respond|escalate",
  "sentiment": "Positive|Neutral|Negative|Angry",
  "risk_level": "Revenue|Reputational|Standard|Low",
  "confidence": 0-100,
  "auto_respond_safe": boolean,
  "financial_topic": boolean,
  "reasoning": "step-by-step analysis",
  "suggested_response": "complete draft reply for all priority levels — label HIGH/MEDIUM drafts as for human review",
  "partial_auto_response": "see rule below",
  "revenue_opportunity": "brief note if revenue potential exists, else empty string"
}

# RULES

## Priority
- RushOrder: customer mentions deadline, occasion (birthday, wedding, anniversary, event), or urgency (rush, ASAP, urgent, need it by, by Friday) in the CURRENT message → ALWAYS HIGH
- HIGH: RushOrder, damage claims, refund disputes, angry/negative tone, reputational risk
- MEDIUM: exchange requests, returns, order status, custom orders, tracking
- LOW: simple FAQ, product questions fully answered from product context or FAQ

## Current message vs conversation history
- Classify intents based ONLY on what the customer is explicitly asking in the CURRENT message
- History is context — it must NOT inflate the priority of the current message's intents
- A ProductQuestion or SimpleFAQ stays LOW even if history has a pending RushOrder, UNLESS the current message itself uses urgency language or directly re-raises the urgent issue (e.g. "still waiting", "I need to know now")

## partial_auto_response rule
- Set this field to an immediate answer for any intent where answerable_from_context=true AND priority is not HIGH
- This applies even when recommended_action=immediate_alert (mixed-intent case)
- Use ONLY verified product/FAQ info — no guessing
- Example: message has RushOrder(HIGH) + ProductQuestion(MEDIUM, answerable) → partial_auto_response = "The mug comes in Blue, Pink, Forest Green, and Natural White"
- Empty string if no answerable non-HIGH intents exist

## Auto-respond
- auto_respond_safe=true when ALL intents in the CURRENT message are LOW AND confidence>=95 AND financial_topic=false AND no Damage/Complaint/Refund/Exchange intents
- FOLLOW-UP RULE: if the current message is all LOW priority AND fully answerable from context, set recommended_action=auto_respond and auto_respond_safe=true EVEN IF conversation history contains HIGH priority issues — the store owner is already handling the urgent matter, do not send them simple FAQ follow-ups too
- If primary_priority=HIGH: recommended_action is ALWAYS immediate_alert — never escalate a HIGH priority message regardless of confidence
- If confidence < 80% AND primary_priority is MEDIUM or LOW: recommended_action=escalate
- Never auto-respond to financial topics

## Output
- Return ONLY valid JSON, no markdown fences`
